Communication: popup and content script communicate ONLY through
chrome.tabs.sendMessage(). They never share code or state directly.
State is persisted in sessionStorage inside the page — if the page
reloads, automation resumes automatically.


THE DATA FORMAT (EXCEL)
-----------------------
- File type: .xlsx only
- Only the FIRST sheet is read
- First row MUST be headers (column names)
- ALL columns become form fields — headers are matched against the
  webpage's input name, id, or placeholder attributes
- A "PRN" column is MANDATORY — it is the unique identifier. This
  column is filled into the PRN input and SKIPPED when filling the form
- Empty rows are filtered out
- Null cells default to "" (empty string)

Example row after parsing:
  { PRN: "101", Name: "John", Email: "john@test.com",
    Phone: "555-0100", Course: "Computer Science" }


THE AUTOMATION LOOP (content.js)
--------------------------------
Each row goes through 3 phases in sequence:

PHASE 1 — enter_prn
  1. Read the PRN from the current row
  2. Wait for the PRN input element (#prn) to appear on the page
  3. Fill in the PRN value
  4. Click the "Next" button (#next), or press Enter if no button exists
  5. Wait for the form to appear

PHASE 2 — fill_form
  1. Wait for form fields OR save button to appear
  2. Loop through every column except "PRN", find matching fields on the
     page (by name, id, or placeholder), and fill them
  3. Click the "Save" button (#save)
  4. Wait for completion — whichever comes first:
       - success message appears
       - URL changes
       - PRN input reappears

PHASE 3 — return_prn
  1. Increment index and processed count
  2. Navigate back — either click the configured backButton or
     call window.history.back()
  3. Wait for PRN input (#prn) to reappear
  4. Loop starts again for the next row

ON ANY FAILURE:
  - The row is recorded in failed[] with the error message
  - Automation continues to the next row
  - If PRN input isn't found after the error, tries history.back()
    as recovery

AUTO-RECOVERY:
  On page load, content.js checks if automation was running (from
  sessionStorage). If yes, it calls runAutomation() to resume.


CONFIG — THE SINGLE CUSTOMISATION POINT
----------------------------------------
Located at the top of content.js (lines 1-7):

  const CONFIG = {
      prnInput: "#prn",
      saveButton: "#save",
      nextButton: "#next",
      backButton: "",
      successMessage: ".success, .alert-success, [role='status']"
  };

  prnInput        CSS selector for the PRN/ID input field
  saveButton      CSS selector for the save/submit button
  nextButton      CSS selector for the "go to form" button
  backButton      CSS selector for "back" button ("" = history.back())
  successMessage  CSS selector(s) that appear after successful save

Everything else derives from this config and the Excel column headers.


FIELD MATCHING ALGORITHM
------------------------
For every <input>, <textarea>, <select> on the page (that isn't
disabled or readonly):

  1. Take the field's name, id, and placeholder attributes
  2. Normalise them (trim + lowercase)
  3. Check if ANY of them match the Excel column name (also normalised)
  4. Return the first match

This means: if your Excel column is "Email", it will match a field with
name="Email" OR id="Email" OR placeholder="Email".


POPUP UI FEATURES
-----------------
  Website          Shows the current page's hostname
  Excel file       Accepts .xlsx only; shows filename + row count
  Mode — Auto      Processes every row in the sheet
  Mode — Single    Dropdown to pick one PRN; processes only that row
  Current PRN      Shows the PRN being processed currently
  Processed        Counter updated live
  Remaining        Counter updated live
  Current Status   Status text stream:
                     "Finding PRN box for 101..."
                     "Submitted PRN 101; waiting for form..."
                     "Waiting for fields for 101..."
                     "Filled 4 fields for 101; saving..."
                     "Returning to PRN page..."
                     "Failed 101; continuing..."
  Progress bar     0–100% based on processed/total
  Start / Stop     Buttons disabled appropriately based on state

Status is polled from content.js every 1 second (via setInterval).


TIMING / WAIT STRATEGY
----------------------
There are NO artificial delays (setTimeout, sleep). All waits use a
MutationObserver on the entire DOM:

  waitForCondition(checkCondition, timeoutMs = 30000)
    → Returns a Promise
    → Resolves when checkCondition() returns truthy
    → Rejects after 30 seconds if condition never met
    → Watches: childList, subtree, attributes mutations on
      document.documentElement

Used in:
  waitForElement(selector)       — waits for a DOM element to appear
  waitForFormFields(row)         — waits for save button OR any field
  waitForSaveComplete(prevUrl)   — waits for success/URL change/PRN input

Default timeout is 30 seconds everywhere.


POPUP ↔ CONTENT SCRIPT MESSAGES
--------------------------------
  GET_PAGE_INFO          popup sends on open
  GET_AUTOMATION_STATUS  popup sends every 1 second (polling)
  START_AUTOMATION       popup sends on Start click, payload: { rows }
  STOP_AUTOMATION        popup sends on Stop click

  All return: { website, prn, processed, total, remaining, status,
                isRunning, failed }


